article.headline: Arizona State 72, Northern Arizona 55
article.story: TEMPE, Ariz. (AP) -- Bryson Krueger scored 16 of his 18 points in the second half as Arizona State beat Northern Arizona 72-55 Thursday night in the championship game of the ASU Hoops Classic. Kevin Kruger added 14 points, seven rebounds and five assists for the Sun Devils (6-3) as he earned tournament MVP honors. Kyle Landry had 13 points and six rebounds for Northern Arizona (6-6). Krueger hit a 3-pointer and had a three-point play on back-to-back possessions during a 10-0 run that gave Arizona State a 47-34 lead with 14:12 remaining. The Lumberjacks closed to within 53-47 on Steven Sir's 3-pointer with 9:00 left but Krueger and Kruger each hit 3-pointers and Northern Arizona never got closer than nine. Krueger missed all four of his shots in the first half but made 6-of-12 in the second half. Sir finished with 12 points -- all on 3-pointers -- for the Lumberjacks, who committed 22 turnovers. Arizona State has won its tournament 29 times in its 39-year history, including 13 of the last 17.
